"title": "7454: sprinkling",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7454: sprinkling",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In the OT, the blood of a sacrificial animal was sprinkled against the altar as a sign of atonement or consecration to the LORD. The NT uses the same image to refer to the gaining of forgiveness through the sacrificial death of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>Sprinkling of an animal's blood as a sign of atonement</h2>\n<h3>On the altar</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:2\">LEV 7:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:6\">EXO 24:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:5\">LEV 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:11\">LEV 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:2\">LEV 3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:8\">LEV 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:13\">LEV 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:9\">LEV 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:12\">LEV 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:18\">LEV 9:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:6\">LEV 17:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:17\">NUM 18:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:13\">2KI 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:15\">2KI 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:22-2Chr29:24\">2CH 29:22–29:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:16\">2CH 30:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:11\">2CH 35:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:18\">EZK 43:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:20\">EZK 43:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:21\">HEB 9:21</a></p>\n<h3>In front of the inner curtain in the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:6\">LEV 4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:17\">LEV 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>Towards the front of the Tent of Meeting</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:4\">NUM 19:4</a></p>\n<h3>On the front of the atonement cover</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:14-Lev16:16\">LEV 16:14–16:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>On the door-frames of the houses where the Passover lamb was eaten</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:7\">EXO 12:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:22\">EXO 12:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:28\">HEB 11:28</a></p>\n<h2>Sprinkling of blood as a sign of consecration</h2>\n<h3>The consecration of people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:8\">EXO 24:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:20-Exod29:21\">EXO 29:20–29:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:23\">LEV 8:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:19\">HEB 9:19</a></p>\n<h3>The consecration of the altar</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:18-Lev16:19\">LEV 16:18–16:19</a></p>\n<h2>Sprinkling of oil as a sign of consecration</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:11\">LEV 8:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:30\">LEV 8:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:15-Lev14:16\">LEV 14:15–14:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:27\">LEV 14:27</a></p>\n<h2>Sprinkling (usually with water) as a sign of cleansing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:7\">NUM 8:7</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:25\">EZK 36:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:7\">LEV 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:51\">LEV 14:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:13\">NUM 19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:18-Num19:21\">NUM 19:18–19:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:15\">ISA 52:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:13\">HEB 9:13</a></p>\n<h2>Sprinkling as an image of forgiveness in Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:11-Heb9:14\">HEB 9:11–9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:18-Heb9:28\">HEB 9:18–9:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:22\">HEB 10:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:24\">HEB 12:24</a></p>\n<h2>Sprinkling of dust as a visible sign of mourning</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:6\">JOS 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:12\">JOB 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:10\">LAM 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:30\">EZK 27:30</a></p>",
